  "title": "Удалить устаревший `--wiki-path` из `update api-manifest`",
  "description": "## T-0994 [ ] P2: Удалить устаревший `--wiki-path` из `update api-manifest`\n\n- Создана: 2026-07-08T19:49:00+03:00\n- Состояние: open\n- Приоритет: P2\n- Execution class: `internal-substrate`\n- Scheduling tier: `later`\n- Зависимости: T-0990\n- Ссылки:\n  - Доменный документ: `docs/documentation/api-manifest.md`\n  - Исходный код: `eng/Electron2D.Build/RepositoryPolicyVerifiers.cs`\n  - Тесты: `tests/Electron2D.Tests.Integration/RepositoryBuildToolTests.cs`\n  - Источник follow-up: `docs/verdicts/release-management/t-0990-audit-r07.md`\n\n### Execution contract\n\n- Task type: build-tooling-cli-cleanup\n- Ready-to-start:\n  - task state is `open`.\n  - manual API profile remains the only source-of-truth introduced by `T-0990`.\n  - a focused CLI regression can cover the legacy `update api-manifest --wiki-path` argument.\n- Stop conditions:\n  - the change would restore Wiki as an input for generated manifest status.\n  - the change would alter public API approval decisions or runtime public API implementation.\n  - the change would silently accept legacy input without an explicit documented no-op contract.\n- May change:\n  - `update api-manifest` argument parser and direct tests/docs.\n  - generated local documentation index if docs are updated.\n  - task notes and diary for this task.\n- Must not change:\n  - `data/api/electron2d-public-api-profile.json` owner decisions.\n  - runtime public API implementation.\n  - saved audit reports.\n- Required outputs:\n  - legacy `--wiki-path` for `update api-manifest` is either rejected with stable diagnostic or explicitly documented as a compatibility no-op.\n  - focused integration test proves the chosen behavior and that Wiki is not read as source-of-truth.\n- Required commands:\n  - focused CLI argument regression.\n  - `dotnet run --project eng/Electron2D.Build -- verify ci-matrix`\n  - `dotnet run --project eng/Electron2D.Build -- verify audit-followups`\n  - `git diff --check`\n- External audit:\n  - not required unless bundled with a parent API tooling package.\n\n### Самодостаточное описание\n\nr07 primary audit for `T-0990` accepted the manual public API profile contract, but noted a cleanup debt: `update api-manifest` still accepts legacy argument `--wiki-path` and carries `ApiManifestArguments.WikiPath`, even though generated manifest status no longer reads Wiki as input. The recommended fix is to reject the stale argument with a stable diagnostic. A documented compatibility no-op is acceptable only if a test proves the Wiki path is not read.\n\n### Internal substrate acceptance contract\n\n- `update api-manifest` command-line surface no longer suggests that Wiki compatibility pages are an input.\n- The manual profile remains the only source for public API inclusion decisions.\n- CI/API manifest documentation matches the chosen CLI behavior.\n\n### Критерии приёмки\n\n- [ ] Focused CLI test covers `update api-manifest --wiki-path .github/wiki --check`.\n- [ ] Legacy argument behavior is stable: rejected diagnostic or documented no-op.\n- [ ] `verify ci-matrix`, `verify audit-followups` and `git diff --check` pass.\n\n### Подзадачи\n\n- [ ] Add RED regression for stale `--wiki-path` on `update api-manifest`.\n- [ ] Remove/reject the argument or document compatibility no-op.\n- [ ] Update docs/generated docs if command contract changes.\n- [ ] Run focused checks and required verifiers.\n\n### Current evidence\n\n- audit-followup-closure:\n  - source: docs/verdicts/release-management/t-0990-audit-r07.md\n  - id: FOLLOW_UP_FINDING F4\n  - state: tracked-new\n  - target: T-0994\n  - rationale: Primary audit r07 accepted `T-0990` and classified stale `--wiki-path` as P3 CLI cleanup. Wiki is not used as source-of-truth, so this task tracks command-surface cleanup without expanding current `T-0990` behavior.\n- audit-followup-closure:\n  - source: docs/verdicts/release-management/t-0990-audit-r08.md\n  - id: FOLLOW_UP_FINDING F4\n  - state: tracked-existing\n  - target: T-0994\n  - rationale: Primary audit r08 repeated the stale `update api-manifest --wiki-path` cleanup finding and explicitly pointed to existing `T-0994`; no new task is needed.\n- audit-followup-closure:\n  - source: docs/verdicts/release-management/t-0990-audit-r09.md\n  - id: FOLLOW_UP_FINDING F4\n  - state: tracked-existing\n  - target: T-0994\n  - rationale: Accepted primary audit r09 repeated the stale `update api-manifest --wiki-path` cleanup finding and explicitly pointed to existing `T-0994`; no new task is needed.\n- audit-followup-closure:\n  - source: docs/verdicts/release-management/t-0990-audit-control-r09.md\n  - id: FOLLOW_UP_FINDING F1\n  - state: tracked-existing\n  - target: T-0994\n  - rationale: Control audit r09 repeated the stale `update api-manifest --wiki-path` cleanup finding and recommended P2 priority. `T-0994` already owns the CLI cleanup, so priority was raised and no new task is needed.\n- audit-followup-closure:\n  - source: docs/verdicts/release-management/t-0990-audit-r10.md\n  - id: FOLLOW_UP_FINDING F4\n  - state: tracked-existing\n  - target: T-0994\n  - rationale: Accepted primary audit r10 repeated the stale `update api-manifest --wiki-path` cleanup finding and explicitly pointed to existing `T-0994`; no new task is needed.\n- audit-followup-closure:\n  - source: docs/verdicts/release-management/t-0990-audit-control-r10.md\n  - id: FOLLOW_UP_FINDING F1\n  - state: tracked-existing\n  - target: T-0994\n  - rationale: Accepted control audit r10 repeated the stale `update api-manifest --wiki-path` cleanup finding and explicitly pointed to the same CLI cleanup owned by `T-0994`; no new task is needed.\n\n### Заметки агента\n\n2026-07-08T19:49:00+03:00 - Создано как `tracked-new` closure для `FOLLOW_UP_FINDING F4` из accepted primary audit r07; finding перенесён в P3 build-tooling CLI cleanup.\n\n2026-07-08T21:26:00+03:00 - Control audit r09 repeated the stale `--wiki-path` cleanup as `FOLLOW_UP_FINDING F1` and recommended P2; existing `T-0994` was raised from P3 to P2 and remains the owner.\n\n",
